      "english_close": "By the word 'māyā' is meant ignorance, indeterminable by being and non-being. For when it is analyzed by reasoning, it cannot be stated, 'it is,' or 'it is not'; nor simply 'it is not,' because, by being different from both being and non-being, it is unfit to be described in those terms. Therefore it is indeterminable, not merely unsayable.",
      "preserved_terms": [
