        }
      ],
      "why_this_passage": "This is the cleanest short statement of Vimuktātman's anirvacanīya-khyāti: the appearing object of error is not reduced either to ordinary being or to simple non-being. It fairly represents his position because it comes in the explicit upasaṃhāra of the khyāti discussion rather than in a polemical caricature of opponents.",
